description.narrative: UNICEF continued to support the strengthening of the legal framework on child protection in China. Major progress was made in the revision of theLaw on the Protection of Minorsthat passed in 2020, with a new chapter on child online protection added that will come into effective in June 2021, with UNICEF’s contribution to technical discussions. UNICEF also provided inputs to the revision of theLaw on Prevention of Juvenile Delinquency, which was approved in December 2020, leading to further policy reform on child justice. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2021
